{
	"info": {
		"_postman_id": "cognito-login-request",
		"name": "AWS Cognito Login (Token Generator)",
		"description": "Generiert JWT Token direkt in Postman über AWS Cognito",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
	},
	"item": [
		{
			"name": "Login - Token generieren",
			"event": [
				{
					"listen": "test",
					"script": {
						"exec": [
							"pm.test(\"Status code is 200\", function () {",
							"    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
							"});",
							"",
							"pm.test(\"Response has AuthenticationResult\", function () {",
							"    var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
							"    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('AuthenticationResult');",
							"});",
							"",
							"// Token automatisch in Environment Variable speichern",
							"if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
							"    var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
							"    if (jsonData.AuthenticationResult && jsonData.AuthenticationResult.IdToken) {",
							"        pm.environment.set('idToken', jsonData.AuthenticationResult.IdToken);",
							"        pm.environment.set('accessToken', jsonData.AuthenticationResult.AccessToken);",
							"        pm.environment.set('refreshToken', jsonData.AuthenticationResult.RefreshToken);",
							"        ",
							"        console.log('✅ Token erfolgreich generiert und in Environment Variable gespeichert!');",
							"        console.log('Token ist gültig für:', jsonData.AuthenticationResult.ExpiresIn, 'Sekunden');",
							"    }",
							"}"
						],
						"type": "text/javascript"
					}
				}
			],
			"request": {
				"auth": {
					"type": "noauth"
				},
				"method": "POST",
				"header": [
					{
						"key": "Content-Type",
						"value": "application/x-amzn-json-1.1",
						"type": "text"
					},
					{
						"key": "X-Amz-Target",
						"value": "AWSCognitoIdentityProviderService.InitiateAuth",
						"type": "text"
					}
				],
				"body": {
					"mode": "raw",
					"raw": "{\n  \"ClientId\": \"{{cognitoClientId}}\",\n  \"AuthFlow\": \"USER_PASSWORD_AUTH\",\n  \"AuthParameters\": {\n    \"USERNAME\": \"{{userEmail}}\",\n    \"PASSWORD\": \"{{userPassword}}\"\n  }\n}",
					"options": {
						"raw": {
							"language": "json"
						}
					}
				},
				"url": {
					"raw": "https://cognito-idp.{{awsRegion}}.amazonaws.com/",
					"protocol": "https",
					"host": [
						"cognito-idp",
						"{{awsRegion}}",
						"amazonaws",
						"com"
					],
					"path": [
						""
					]
				},
				"description": "⚠️ **WICHTIG:** Diese Methode funktioniert nur, wenn AWS Cognito App Client so konfiguriert ist, dass `USER_PASSWORD_AUTH` ohne Client Secret erlaubt ist.\n\n**Alternative (Empfohlen):** Token aus Browser holen (siehe `TOKEN_GENERIERUNG.md`)\n\n**Verwendung:**\n1. Setze Environment Variables: `userEmail`, `userPassword`, `cognitoClientId`, `awsRegion`\n2. Führe Request aus\n3. Token wird automatisch in `idToken` Environment Variable gespeichert"
			},
			"response": []
		}
	],
	"variable": [
		{
			"key": "cognitoClientId",
			"value": "7kc5tt6a23fgh53d60vkefm812",
			"type": "string"
		},
		{
			"key": "awsRegion",
			"value": "eu-central-1",
			"type": "string"
		},
		{
			"key": "userEmail",
			"value": "",
			"type": "string"
		},
		{
			"key": "userPassword",
			"value": "",
			"type": "secret"
		}
	]
}

